{
  "stem": "21788.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was 12.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was known that, of course, things were bad.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You had your business taken away from you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You got beaten up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "People disappeared.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "People were put into work camps.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "People were interrogated and tortured and were never the same afterwards.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the idea of the death camps really did not-- was not known until 1944 or '45 when it became known and everybody denied it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "How can such a thing happen?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So no, no, no.l We did not know, in Shanghai, what happened.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "What did happen, of course, was the fact that yes, we were allowed to come to Shanghai, the occupied part by the Japanese.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were allowed to come to Shanghai by the Japanese-- not the Chinese, the Japanese-- with most of us declaring our intentions of coming to the United States as early as whenever it is possible.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And matter of fact, we have to thank my mother for that.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That she was so absolutely devastated by having to stay in Shanghai for who knows how many years, that she immediately-- I mean, the second or third week that we were able to get around in Shanghai-- went to the American Council and got a number, a waiting number, to be put on the waiting list to come to the United States whenever possible.",
      "word_count": 64
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The idea being that you take out a waiting list number, and you already, having in your possession documents, resource, permission to come to United States, which we didn't have.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But she took out a number anyway, which stood us in very good deed when the war was over.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were called two years after the war was over in 1947.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "When we were called to come present our documents, we didn't have any.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
